  <div class="row justify-content-center mb-4">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-10 px-4">
      <p>
       Prior to 2011, New York had made the playoffs in 15 of the last 16 seasons. In that time, the Yankees won 11 AL East Division titles and won two World Series titles, but made it to five. But, it could have been even more successful: New York lost twice in the World Series and was up 3-0 against the Boston Red Sox in the American League Championship series. Plus, the Yankees were one of two teams to win two World Series from 2000 to 2010 (the Red Sox won two in 2004 and 2007).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

