  <div class="row justify-content-center mb-4">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-10 px-4">
      <p>
       After leaving their mark from 2000 to 2010, the Yankees had a less successful decade in the next decade. From 2011 to 2020, New York missed the playoffs three years, won only three division titles, and didn’t make it to baseball’s biggest stage. As a whole, they averaged 88 wins per season (using the number of wins the Yankees were on pace for in the shortened 2020 season), and their winning percentage dropped to 56 percent in this decade, compared to winning an average of 96 games per season, and just under 61 percent of games the decade prior. So, how did this happen?
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>


